Durban - Two girls, aged 5 and 7, were killed when a wall collapsed onto them in Durban's suburb of Clare Estate on Monday afternoon. 

The two were playing in the driveway of a home with another child, when tragedy struck.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

Rescue Care Operations Director, Garrith Jamieson, said the children were crushed by the wall. 

"Unfortunately two of the young children had sustained major injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for them and they were declared deceased on the scene. The third child had sustained moderate injuries and was stabilised on the scene before being transported to a nearby hospital for the further care that she required," he said. 

Two children were killed when a wall collapsed on them on Monday.
Picture: Rescue Care



Meanwhile, four men have been arrested following a hijacking and alleged kidnapping in Madadeni, just outside Newcastle on Monday morning. 

Read: KZN police search for missing children
A source close to the investigation revealed that the four men were nabbed not far from where the hijacking occurred. He said police did not want divulge further information as more arrests were expected. He added that the children were unharmed. 
